text: Sam Crump was a member of the Arizona State Senate from 2007 through 2010. He was elected to the Senate in November 2006, and won re-election in 2008. He resigned in January 2010, in order to run for the U.S. House of Representatives, for the seat being vacated by John Shadegg. ==References== Category:Arizona Republicans Category:Members of the Arizona House of Representatives Category:Living people Category:Year of birth missing (living people)
title: Sam Crump
